# planning-check-already-shipped-before-planning — History

## v1.3.0 (2026-06-15)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1357 planning session (continued) — after the status-note
reshape (v1.2.0), the plan-loop reviewer returned a SECOND NOGO, this time Grade F, because the
submitted plan artifact was an empty placeholder: the planner had paused its turn on a background
`pytest`/Monitor full-suite count and the artifact contained zero plan content.
**Verification:** verified-local (the fix was confirmed when the very next iteration produced a
complete, gradeable plan; the background-suite count itself remained unconfirmed at the boundary,
which is exactly the open-risk-flagging the lesson prescribes)

### What changed

- Added the core NEW lesson (Verified-Workflow step 11): never gate the emission of a due artifact
  on an in-flight background job. Emit the COMPLETE forward-looking plan from evidence in hand; a
  still-running gate becomes a flagged open-risk line inside Verification, never a reason to output
  a placeholder. An empty/placeholder artifact fails EVERY rubric dimension and is an automatic
  Grade F — strictly worse than the v1.2.0 status-note NOGO.
- Added the generalizable rule distinguishing "no deadline → may keep working/waiting" from
  "artifact due THIS turn (your output IS the posted artifact) → must emit now from evidence in
  hand + flag open risk."
- Added a When-to-Use trigger: "you're tempted to wait on a background job / Monitor / long test run
  before producing a due plan or review artifact."
- Added a Failed Attempts row: paused the turn on a background `pytest`/Monitor for a full-suite
  count → submitted the placeholder "Output not yet flushed…" → plan-loop Grade F.
- Added a Results & Parameters subsection documenting the Grade F NOGO, the placeholder text, the
  root cause, the verified fix, and the generalizable rule.
- Extended the planner decision tree with the "artifact DUE this turn + background job running"
  branch; added a Verified On row for the Grade F NOGO and its fix.
- Frontmatter: bumped `version` 1.2.0 → 1.3.0, kept `date` 2026-06-15, broadened `description`
  (added clause 5 about background-job placeholders → Grade F), kept `verification: verified-local`.

### Why

v1.2.0 covered the FIRST NOGO (a retrospective status note is a category error → Grade D). It did
not cover what happens when a planner, trying to get a fuller verification, blocks the emission of a
due artifact on a pending background task. The #1357 session learned that doing so produces an empty
placeholder artifact, which is STRICTLY WORSE — an automatic Grade F that fails every rubric
dimension and addresses none of the prior findings. The fix is to treat already-collected evidence
as sufficient to emit a complete draft and to demote a still-running gate to a flagged open-risk
line item, never withholding the whole artifact. This was verified when the very next iteration
produced a complete, gradeable plan.

